So I've tested positive for covid. My review so far: this is some weird shit. It's all burning skin, tingly legs and fatigue like there's something wrong with gravity. My sinuses feel like they're full of salt and I can't sleep. I just hallucinate for 8 hours then it's morning.
@angharadyeo Hey sorry for the bat tweet. You’re right, it was poor taste and I deleted it

Day 6 of coronavirus and I've lost all taste and smell. Just tried smelling a bag of coffee and it was like sniffing at a bag of sand. Food is polystyrene-flavoured with a hint of salt or sweet. All subtitles gone.

The worst thing about coronavirus is not sleeping. I just spend hour after hour bathed in sweat solving complicated domestic problems to the rhythm of the ceiling fan, which makes a ticking noise as it spins: tickity tick where have my shoes gone tickity tick

Day 2 of my new identity as guy with coronavirus and I think I can pinpoint how I got this. Heathrow to Dubai, a man mid-50s, sitting over the aisle coughing the whole flight. He was coughing so brazenly I assumed he had some socially acceptable ailment like asthma 1/2
